            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened add the <strong>potato cubes</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min or until the potato is beginning to brown</p>",
